Theorem. 
The vacuum expectation value of a charged scalar field with 
the cluster property vanishes in a two-dimensional
relativistic quantum field theory with a conserved charge 
with respect to the continuous symmetry.  
Proof of Theorem. 
I evaluate terms in an uncertainty relation in the vacuum,
instead of Coleman's correlation inequality
 
